HEADWORD: Avowance
<hw>A*vow"ance</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Act
of avowing; avowal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Upholding; defense; vindication.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Can my <qex>avowance</qex> of king-murdering be collected from
anything here written by me?</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Avowant</ent>⟦br⟧
